gf - Git Fixup

USAGE:
    gf [count] [-m=message]

DESCRIPTION:
    Create fixup commits to squash. Uses APP_CONTEXT environment
    variable to inject contextual information into commit message.

ARGUMENTS:
    count
        Number of commits to squash

OPTIONS:
    -m=message
        Commit message to use (uses parent commit message if null)

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-install-context=CONTEXT
        Context information to inject into commit message

NOTE:
    Makes use of APP_CONTEXT environment variable for contextual information.

EXAMPLES:
    gf 3
    gf 2 -m="Fix typo"
    gf 5 -m="Update documentation"